jmandel pushed to branch master

  • @11932: get validator to generate snapshots
@Josh Mandel that commit was me, not you. A bug in the bot somewhere?
In the logic for the github hook (which we maintain in a fork). The underlying hook in zulip changed, and in rewriting the FHIR specific logic I must have introduced a problem.
Yeah, I've relied on Zulip's logic to grab the "pusher" (for most github integrations this is a good idea because individual commits, along with their committers, are listed).

Will fix it this (later today I hope). I think I'll fix it by making sure that our sync process uses a "fhir sync" github user who can do the push, and then adding a committer next to each line (goal being to minimize the number of changes to the underlying zulip code base)
